  "text": "In the LLVM optimization pass system, pass registration and execution follows a templated, concept-based polymorphism pattern:\n\n## PassManager Template (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h)\nThe core PassManager is a template class parameterized by IRUnitT (e.g., Module, Function). It implements addPass<PassT>() which wraps each pass in a PassModel<IRUnitT, PassT> that derives from PassConcept. Passes are stored as unique_ptr<PassConcept> in a vector.\n\n## PassConcept and PassModel (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerInternal.h)\nPassConcept is an abstract base class defining the polymorphic run() interface. PassModel is a template that wraps any pass class and implements the concept, calling the pass's run() method. This enables storing heterogeneous pass types in a single container.\n\n## PassInfoMixin (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h)\nAll pass classes derive from PassInfoMixin<DerivedT>, which provides name() and printPipeline() methods. Example: InstCombinePass : public PassInfoMixin<InstCombinePass> (llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombine.h)\n\n## Pass Registration via PassRegistry.def (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def)\nPasses are defined using MODULE_PASS, FUNCTION_PASS, CGSCC_PASS, and LOOP_PASS macros that map string names to pass constructors (e.g., MODULE_PASS(\"instcombine\", InstCombinePass()))\n\n## Optimization Pipeline (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp)\nThe O2/O3 pipeline is constructed through buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() which calls:\n- buildModuleSimplificationPipeline() - adds early optimization passes\n- buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() - adds main optimization passes including ControlHeightReduction (O3 only), loop passes, vectorization, and global optimizations\n\nPasses are added via MPM.addPass(PassInstance()), which creates PassModel wrappers and stores them in the PassManager's Passes vector.\n\n## Pass Parsing and Lookup (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp)\nparseModulePass() looks up pass names in PassRegistry.def using a macro-expanded switch statement. When a match is found, it instantiates the pass and calls MPM.addPass() to add it to the pipeline.\n\n## Execution (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h)\nPassManager<IRUnitT>::run() iterates through all Passes, calling Pass->run(IR, AnalysisManager) for each. Each pass's PreservedAnalyses return value is used to invalidate cached analyses. This enables the dependency-aware, lazy evaluation of analysis passes."
}

